page.title: 01WARWICK BRIDGE AREA
page.content: The area is a rural one with several small dormitory villages for Carlisle. The River Eden,one of the few in the country that flow North,runs through the area and if you can afford it there is good salmon fishing. There is no Primary Industry apart from Farming. There is variety in every aspect of the area,especially in houses and jobs. People live in the area but tend to leave it for work or entertainment. Pretty though it is there is little tourism,people pass through without stopping. A major feature of the area is the Trunk road A69 Carlisle to Newcastle. It provides speedy commuter travel and keeps the lanes free of traffic but is dangerous for children and speeds potential visitors away.
